      "side": 1,
      "message": "This was pulled directly from chromium\u0027s zlib BUILD.gn.  I\u0027m happy to remove the assert and should have done so already.\n\nThis if statement also gets executed for armv7.  Oddly, zlib enables ARMV8 defines for armv7 and then in the .c file checks for __aarch64__ and/or uses runtime cpu feature detection to handle it accordingly.\n\nIf I understand the code correctly without this cflag a linux gcc build targeting armv7 will hit a #error when compiling.  I\u0027m inclined to keep it to match chromium\u0027s BUILD.gn, but given that our bots won\u0027t build it I can see the argument for removing it as well.",
